cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the analysis of video content and the use of eye-gaze data to predict affective responses to advertisements. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) are less likely but still possible categories, as the paper mentions the use of linguistic and social cues in advertising.
